Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Sta Croce in Gerusalemme (Rom) Grasse. - "

- Reproductions of artworks in Grasse
- Extracts from different publications about Rubens' artworks in Grasse and in Santa Croce in Gerusalemme (Rome)
- Bibliographic references
- Correspondence with Museum Boymans (dated 1943), Goudstikker (dated 1943)
- Draft text "Die Kreuzaufrichtung von Rubens im Hospital zu Grasse"
- Description of Rubens' 'St. Helena' on a piece of paper (from a book or a booklet)
